      <textAnnotation id="sid-D1BC5CC8-218E-45BF-A93D-9D676CC2CC27" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Relabeling: Develop Continuous Improvement Plan For all Suppliers</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-3BFBE22A-D3F1-467E-B933-0EF42A501167" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Relabeling : Analyze Continuous Improvement Plans</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-0907919B-7509-420F-9420-6CC530078CEB" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>L3 Process Description-
This is the process of reviewing a supplier's performance against a mutually agreed-upon corrective action plan to identify those who are exceeding, meeting or not meeting the action plan. Meet and communicate with suppliers to discuss inadequate performance in a purchasing relationship. Develop an action plan to correct the identified deficiencies.
Identify problems that may be caused, not necessarily by the supplier, but by the company, the freight carrier, etc. An outcome of this process should be a mutually agreed-upon corrective action plan.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-9EE09B84-CEBD-4640-A6A5-40093F2B3CDE" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Boundary apps (not S4 interface)
- Online supplier report card
- Supplier 360 (SAM, SDM)
- PowerBi dashboard
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-68D98CEF-CFE4-4E5D-8A43-989FC9763887" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-040-200 Develop Corrective Action Plan (CAP) for Problem Suppliers</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-275E2D1D-0A6E-414D-810F-ACAC7038B16E" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
